      • leave

        protected java.lang.Boolean leave(IRNode parent,
                                  IRNode n,
                                  java.lang.Boolean r,
                                  AggregateVisitor<java.lang.Boolean> v_)
        Description copied from class: AggregateVisitor
        Called after finishing traversal of the subtree rooted at n. When AggregateVisitor.enter(IRNode, IRNode) creates a new visitor to be used on the subtree, the old visitor still receives the call to leave() -- that is, leave() always executed the same number of times as AggregateVisitor.enter(IRNode, IRNode). This node provides the final opportunity of placing an updated node in the output AST.
        Overrides:
        leave in class AggregateVisitor<java.lang.Boolean>
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent AST node of n or null when it is the root.
        n - The original node in the input AST
        r - The result returned by IRNode.aggregateChildren(AggregateVisitor)
        v_ - The new node visitor created by AggregateVisitor.enter(IRNode, IRNode), or this.
